# Solentra — Windsurf Rules

## Project
Solentra is an AI-first EHR built on Medplum v5.1.6 (FHIR, React, TypeScript, Mantine v8).
Owner: Logan Carton, Psychiatric NP. Built for a real clinical practice — HIPAA applies.

## Key Files
- `packages/app/src/solentra/ProviderDashboard.tsx` — main dashboard
- `packages/app/src/solentra/PatientChart.tsx` — patient chart
- `packages/app/src/solentra/VisitNote.tsx` — visit note writer
- `packages/app/src/solentra/clinicalAlerts.ts` — alerts engine
- `packages/app/src/solentra/dashboardData.ts` — FHIR dashboard hook
- `packages/app/src/solentra/patientData.ts` — FHIR patient hook
- `packages/app/src/AppRoutes.tsx` — routes

## Rules

### No Bloat (critical)
- Never create a new file when an existing file is the right place.
- When replacing a feature, delete the old code entirely. No dead code, no overrides stacked below old code.
- No duplicate types or data across files — one definition, imported everywhere.
- No abstractions for single uses. No passthrough wrappers.

### TypeScript
- No `any`. Run `npx tsc --noEmit -p packages/app/tsconfig.json` and fix all errors before finishing.

### Stack
- UI: Mantine v8 only.
- Icons: @tabler/icons-react only.
- FHIR: Medplum hooks only (`useSearchResources`, `useSearchOne`).
- Always keep demo data fallback working alongside live FHIR data.

### Git
- No commits with TypeScript errors.
- Meaningful commit messages.
- Never commit secrets or .env files.
